      <h3>What is cadence?</h3>
      <p>In cycling, cadence is the number of revolutions of the crank per minute; this is the rate at which a cyclist is pedalling/turning the pedals. Cadence is directly proportional to wheel speed, but is a distinct measurement and changes with gearingâ€”which determines the ratio of crank rpm to wheel rpm.</p>
